views.name: tech-deploy-oop-layer
views.documentation: This diagram shows a variation of how the application components defined in the ISA can be deployed to nodes in the technology architecture. In this variant the Member State of the Data Provider provides a National OOP Layer that realizes the functionality needed to connect to the TOOP network, i.e the TOOP Connector, SMP and AP.

views.name: tech-deploy-local
views.documentation: This diagram shows a variation of how the application components defined in the ISA can be deployed to nodes in the technology architecture. In this variant the Comptetent Authority acting as the Data Consumer operates its own SMP and AP.

views.documentation: This diagram shows a variation of how the application components defined in the ISA can be deployed to nodes in the technology architecture. views.name: tech-deploy-shared
views.documentation: This diagram shows a variation of how the application components defined in the ISA can be deployed to nodes in the technology architecture. In this variant the SMP and AP are hosted by the Member State, i.e. shared by the Competent Authorities from that MS.
